Enum TimerState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TimerState>
      • org.oddjob.scheduling.state.TimerState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TimerState>, State

    public enum TimerState
extends Enum<TimerState>
implements State
    Encapsulate the allowed states for Timers.
    Author:
    Rob Gordon

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ACTIVE
      Indicates that child jobs are active.
      COMPLETE
      The timer is complete and the child job is complete.
      DESTROYED
      The timer has been destroyed.
      EXCEPTION
      The timer failed to Start or the timer is complete but is reflecting the child's exception state.
      INCOMPLETE
      The timer is complete but is reflecting that the child job is incomplete.
      STARTABLE
      The timer can be started.
      STARTED
      The timer has started.
      STARTING
      The timer is starting.

      • STARTABLE

        public static final TimerState STARTABLE
        The timer can be started. A timer can not be started unless it is in this state.

      • STARTING

        public static final TimerState STARTING
        The timer is starting.

      • ACTIVE

        public static final TimerState ACTIVE
        Indicates that child jobs are active. A Timer will only show this state when it has completed but a child job is being re-run.

      • STARTED

        public static final TimerState STARTED
        The timer has started.

      • INCOMPLETE

        public static final TimerState INCOMPLETE
        The timer is complete but is reflecting that the child job is incomplete.

      • COMPLETE

        public static final TimerState COMPLETE
        The timer is complete and the child job is complete.

      • EXCEPTION

        public static final TimerState EXCEPTION
        The timer failed to Start or the timer is complete but is reflecting the child's exception state.

      • DESTROYED

        public static final TimerState DESTROYED
        The timer has been destroyed. It can no longer be used.
